content: we now begin our lesson with new opening.
because it can seach Fa Lun Gong!
For the introduction, I copy the part from my book about d1:

Although traditional theory considers this opening to be very powerful for black, there are lots of unanswered problems in there. In my opinion d1 is one of the most difficult openings in renju. There are so many variants of straight attack to be learned, as the positional style is impossible in most cases. Most of the problems in this opening come from the different aspect considering the board edges (for example the difference between 4-H and 4-I). I am sure that in the future we will have the answers to the problems of d1 and we can consider this opening to be almost black win, but until then, d1 seems to have a right to be playable even in high level tournaments.
Even if the black win will be proved, I am sure there will still be lots of gamblers to continue playing this opening as remembering all the wins here is really difficult.
I give you some time to read the text above...
